Examining SST Rate of Change

Compiled on Tue Dec 13 11:24:11 2016 by afflerbach

Objective: Compare different methods of deriving SST pressure layer. For the Ocean Health Index global, we compare the number of weekly SST anomalies in the most recent 5 years to the # of anomalies in the furthest 5 years (1985-1989). If we looked at rate of change in anomalies and rescaled according to rate, would that be a big difference?

1 Calculate mean annual SST and SST anomalies (SSTA)

For OHI we only calculated standard deviation so we had to calculate mean here.

## [1] TRUE

2 Original method

Compare the number of weekly anomalies in a 5 year time period as it compares to the historical reference.

3 SST Rate of change

Calculates the trend per pixel from 1982 - 2012 for SST

4 SST Difference in rate of change

Look at rate of change in only the last 10 years (2003-2012) compared to rate of change 1982-1991

This plot shows that over the years 2003-2012, the NE region is warming at a faster rate, -0.05 degrees faster per year, than from 1982-1991.

To see how different the outcome is if we compare the first and last 5 years, we do the same thing but using 1982-1986 and 2008-2012.

This plot shows that over the years 2008-2012, the NE region is warming at a faster rate, 0 degrees faster per year, than from 1982-1986.

5 SST Rescale using difference in rate - 5 years

I ran the same exploration but with SSTA (sea surface temperature anomalies)

6 SSTA Rate of change

Calculates the trend per pixel from 1982 - 2012

The mean change in SST anomaly is 0.03 degrees per year

7 SSTA Difference in rate of change

Look at rate of change in only the last 10 years (2003-2012) compared to rate of change 1982-1991?

This plot shows that over the years 2003-2012, the NE region is warming at a faster rate, 0.18 degrees faster per year, than from 1982-1991.

To see how different the outcome is if we compare the first and last 5 years, we do the same thing but using 1982-1986 and 2008-2012.

This plot shows that over the years 2008-2012, the NE region is warming at a faster rate, 0.12 degrees faster per year, than from 1982-1986.
